{"image_id": "KSU_2007_page_41", "image_size": [1275, 1650], "ocr": [{"text": "Mexico may experience high levels of inflation in the future which could adversely affect KCS’ results of", "bbox": [174.0, 144.5, 1097.1, 165.4]}, {"text": "operations.", "bbox": [174.0, 169.4, 269.5, 190.3]}, {"text": "Mexico has a history of high levels of inflation and may experience high inflation in the future. During", "bbox": [194.9, 208.5, 1078.4, 229.3]}, {"text": "most of the 1980s and during the mid and late 1990s, Mexico experienced periods of high levels of inflation.", "bbox": [153.2, 233.5, 1086.2, 254.4]}, {"text": "The annual rates of inflation for the last three years, as measured by changes in the National Consumer Price", "bbox": [153.2, 258.6, 1087.1, 279.4]}, {"text": "Index, as provided by Banco de Mexico, were 3.8% in 2007, 4.0% in 2006, and 3.3% in 2005. A substantial", "bbox": [153.2, 283.5, 1081.0, 304.3]}, {"text": "increase in the Mexican inflation rate would have the effect of increasing some of KCSM’s costs, which could", "bbox": [153.2, 308.5, 1097.3, 329.4]}, {"text": "adversely affect its results of operations and financial condition. High levels of inflation may also affect the", "bbox": [153.2, 333.6, 1073.5, 354.4]}, {"text": "balance of trade between Mexico and the United States, and other countries, which could adversely affect", "bbox": [153.2, 358.5, 1056.7, 379.3]}, {"text": "KCSM’s results of operations.", "bbox": [153.2, 383.5, 409.7, 404.4]}, {"text": "Item 1B.", "bbox": [153.2, 436.0, 231.0, 456.8]}, {"text": "Unresolved Staff Comments", "bbox": [251.8, 436.0, 495.2, 456.8]}, {"text": "None.", "bbox": [194.9, 475.1, 245.2, 495.9]}, {"text": "Item 2.", "bbox": [153.2, 527.5, 217.1, 548.4]}, {"text": "Properties", "bbox": [238.0, 527.5, 326.0, 548.4]}, {"text": "Property information is provided for each of KCS’ two business segments, the United States (“U.S.”) and", "bbox": [194.9, 566.6, 1095.4, 587.5]}, {"text": "Mexico.", "bbox": [153.2, 591